reviewText: Accurate account of history, my cats liked it too.

I lived that, I was a b-36 crew chief 1953 to 1956 492717 rb-36f , I read a nd agreed with it, the peace maker and that it was, I was on 48hr missions that is a long time no refueling, with a H-bomb in her bomb bay

I didn't know that a tornado destroyed the B-36 factory.  What a whale of a plane; Cold War monster.  Jimmy Stewart movie is interesting too, and even .... spoiler alert...  has a crash.  June Allyson is not in this one.
Somewhat disappointing with poor quality footage.  I've seen much better.
The magazine arrived OK.  No problems
Excellent history of this giant!  I remember seeing '36s flying out of Carswell AFB in the 1950s and will never forget the unique noise their engines made.  A welcome addition, indeed.
